{
  "title": "Dont box yourself in",
  "slug": "dont-box-yourself-in",
  "publishedAt": "2020-09-24T07:11:06.000Z",
  "excerpt": "Our culture exists, in large part, by putting people in boxes.",
  "image": "",
  "readTime": "2 min",
  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Our culture exists, in large part, by putting people in boxes.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "People—parents, recruiters, psychologists—put people in boxes all the time. It helps them categorize the world and make sense of people.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And so we have personality scales and ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "assessments",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ", taxonomies and continuums, IQ scores, and all kinds of titles. But either way, what we’re doing is finding ways to distinguish people—to sort them out—by putting a label on a lifestyle, a career, or a quirk.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
        {
          "_key": "link-0",
          "_type": "link",
          "href": "https://blog.brendanbockes.com/pattern-recognition/"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And it’s not just other people. We put ourselves in boxes, too.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Consider that if you’re a writer, you tend to think of yourself as a ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "writer",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " (and not much else). Or, perhaps you’re a musician or a dancer or a zoology professor who thinks you could never do anything new.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
      "markDefs": [
        {
          "_key": "link-0",
          "_type": "link",
          "href": "https://blog.brendanbockes.com/i-am-not-a-lawn-mower/"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "This is just fine if you want to just be a writer or a musician or a dancer…but it can be a disservice to you and your capacity to learn if you’d prefer to do something else.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "People—parents, recruiters, psychologists—need these systems of categorization. (Just as teachers presumably ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "need",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " to grade their students on their tests.) Otherwise there’d be no way to sort and sift through the clutter. To rank people. Or to grasp—in short time—",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "who",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " a person is.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "So, while all the classifying and ordering and grading and grouping ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "might",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " help ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "some",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " people do their jobs better, it can be beneficial to at least acknowledge when and if it’s helping ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "you",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ".",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Because, it ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "really is",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " all invented. One big scheme.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "If a story or a label or a title doesn’t resonate with you—with who you think you are, or who you'd like be—you certainly have the the right to change it (or add to it).",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It’s your life, after all. No sense defining it by any other label than one made and defined by ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "you",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ".",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "…",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Aside: Something I’ve noticed is that if you give yourself ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "permission",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " to write or code or dance (or whatever it is you would like to do), and you do it often, you’ll generally have a much easier time ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "thinking",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " like one, ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "acting",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " like one, and ",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "being",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": " like one. (Which, if you think about it, is the only way anyone has ever become much of anything, anyway.)",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}